virtual machine
1. they works independently
2. little more than a file
3. be configured to use not only a different operating system

two types hypervisor: type
type 1 and type 2
type 1: bare metal as os, e.g xen, vmware's esxi, microsoft's hyper-V, KVM
type 2: hosted hypervisor, most frequently referred to as virtual machine monitor
VMware wrokstation, vmware player, virtualbox, parallel desktop

advantage:
1. Saving money
2. Simplified management
3. threat isolation
4. Backup and recovery
disadvantages
1. compromise performance
2. complexity
3. risk
4. license cost